JO  - Management Science
SP  - 38
EP  - 43
VL  - 5
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The well known chemical equilibrium problem is expressed in the form of minimizing the free energy of a mixture in order to compute the chemical composition at equilibrium. By piece-wise linear approximations to the free energy function, the problem becomes a linear program which can be solved by a standard code on a computing machine. Successive approximations give any degree of accuracy.
